			<p class="plain_text">I am a game programmer at the beginning of my career with a dream of becoming a part of something special and mindblowing in the gaming industry. I live and breathe videogames: as a career and as a hobby.
			<br><br>I started my somewhat professional adventure at school in <b>Metropolia University of Applied Sciences</b> as an Information and Communication Technology Engineer (<b>Bachelor's degree</b>, about to graduate at the end of <b>2022</b>).
			<br> Success in school gave me the opportunity to choose a major freely and this obviously meant <b>Game Development</b>, even though I was adviced otherwise ("You should rather go for <b>Software Development</b> as they have more job openings, yada yada yada...", no regrets).
			<br><br>I currently work at <a class="link" href="https://airdice.com/" target="_blank">Air Dice Games</a> as a game programmer, designing and building awesome online gambling games. My favourite detail about this position is the heavy emphasis on sales oriented game design (a newly found passion for me).</p>			
